race.comment: BANXI (1) is still a maiden after 10 starts but was good here fresh and not far away last time in town. Seems to have come back well and should be ready to peak at the third run in having found a fairly winnable affair here. SIAM EMERALD (4) is going well in three runs this time in, never finishing further back than fourth. He stuck on well last time at Pakenham when beaten 1.5 lengths and should be in this for a long way from the good gate.  ALWAYS TIRED (6) debuted at Moe over 1600m and ran a credible race, sticking on for a midfield finish. The extra trip should be in his favour now and he can improve. FLIGHT SERGEANT (8) will find this much easier than the Melbourne Classic at Caulfield last time. His prior form reads well.
